Coding Exercise 5: Really Hard - Implementing 'Pluck'

This is a hard one!
Implement a 'pluck' function. Pluck should accept an array and a string representing a property name
and return an array containing that property form each object.

Example:

var paints = [
    { color : 'red' },
    { color: 'blue' },
    { color: 'yellow'}]
    
    pluck(paints, 'color');


function pluck(array, property) {
    return array.map(arrayIndex => {
        return arrayIndex[`${property}`];
    })
}

